🎄✨ on the second day of #FITMAS my trainer gave to meeee…. A super set work out that works everything! ✨🎄

Grab your timer and dumbbells for this killer 💪🏽 here’s how it goes 👇🏽:

30 seconds DB Deadlifts
30 seconds Kick Thru Push-ups
20 seconds rest
Repeat 5x

1 min of rest 

30 seconds Alternating Halo Back Lunge
30 seconds Back Fly Step Outs
20 seconds rest 
Repeat 5x

1 min of rest 

30 seconds Rotational Planks
30 seconds Tricep Crabs
20 seconds rest

1 min of rest 

1 min of plank jacks
1 min of straight leg bicycles
1 min of flutter kicks

AND DONE! 🥵💦

Enjoy my friends!

On the fourth day of #fitmas my trainer gave to meee… My 4 Foundational Lifts!

What does this mean, Jess?

Well the Four Foundation Lifts are some of the most basic movement, Upper Body “Pull”, Upper Body “Push”, Lower Body “Pull”, Lower Body “Push”. All other exercises stem from these movements.

An example: A squat is a lower body push which can then modified into a lunge, a glute bridge, a Single Leg step up but they are all stemming from the original movement of that “push”.

If you are feeling lost in the gym or want to create a well-rounded workout try to grab one exercise from each category! Examples Below:

Barbell Squat, Single Leg Deadlift, Kneeling Push Up, Lat Pull Down

Or

DB Deadlifts, Walking Lunges, Military Presses, Seated Row

The combinations are endless! Need help? I’d be happy to give you more info!

Happy Birthday, Mom!! 

You have always been my role model ❤️ love you so much!

Have you ever FELT a song playing? You have this moment where words can’t describe your feelings but the song makes you feel the same way?

This is exactly how I felt during our hot springs hike a couple weekends ago. I felt so small and so present but my heart was screaming with love and appreciation. 

Full transparency, the day before was rough. Like really emotionally and mentally discouraging and draining. The gratitude I felt the next day is a reminder of the ups and downs and adventure that our life. With every bad day I wish you a 100 good ones ❄️

These @vessi shoes are a legit game changer for my cold weather friends. Durable (and waterproof!) enough for a hike, comfortable enough to change into post ski/board, and cute enough to wear out to dinner 😛

Last month I accepted the Fitness + Wellness Manager position at @aquaviewellness! 

It’s been quite the journey from 10 years as a personal trainer, 8 years as a group fitness coach, 5 years as a nutritionist and of course owning my own business to be transitioning out of that role and into this new adventure. 

Not training clients or teaching classes anymore has been so bittersweet 😭but I get to inspire and motivate in a different way. Empowerment was always the end goal with my clients 🙌🏼

Thank you to everyone who has supported my journey and continue to push me to grow more and more!!!

It’s hard to put down our little screens or stop comparing or sit in silence and journal. 

So consider this just a little piece of my universe coming into your universe to say, “I think you are awesome”. 

Now try to believe it 💕
